    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) is accepted given the regulatory precedent for ASTM F1717 as a standardized bench test and the medium model-risk classification. All three primary QoIs satisfy pre-established acceptance bounds (percent difference < 10%; E/uval < 1.96). The assessment team notes that aleatory variability in the force-at-40-mm result was evaluated qualitatively rather than through a structured UQ framework; this is flagged for resolution in a future revision of the credibility package.",
